    <name>Optional Readings</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;Check out these additional articles on strategy instruction, if you are interested, or save them for later review.&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p style="text-align: left; font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;Check out these additional articles on strategy instruction, if you are interested, or save them for later review. We have included them here so you can pursue your interests. &lt;span size="4"&gt;&lt;a title="Assignment 3" href="https://ovae-moodle-dev.myquotient.net/mod/assign/view.php?id=593" target="_blank"&gt;Assignment 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; asks you to read and reflect on onr of these articles, so choose that assignment if you are interested in learning about the research that supports strategy instruction!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 style="text-align: left; font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;Writing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left; font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="text-align: left; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;
&lt;ul style="font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;a title="Chapter 7 NCSALL Metacognition" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Metacognition_Cognitive_Strategy_Instruction_annd_Reading_in_Adult_Literacy.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Metacognition, Cognitive Strategy Instruction, and Reading in Adult Literacy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; a chapter by Jennifer Cromley (2005), from the NCSALL Review of Research, chapter 7. Access it online at &lt;a href="http://www.ncsall.net/fileadmin/resources/ann_rev/rall_v5_ch7_supp.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span size="4"&gt;http://www.ncsall.net/fileadmin/resources/ann_rev/rall_v5_ch7_supp.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul style="text-align: left; font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Read the following article on writing strategy instruction for adult literacy level learners. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/sites/default/files/ALstrategy_sum_teachers.pdf" title="Strategy Instruction in Writing for Adult Literacy Learners: A Summary" target="_blank"&gt;Strategy Instruction in Writing for Adult Literacy Learners: A Summary&lt;/a&gt;, by Charles A. MacArthur is a summary of the full study published as: MacArthur, C.A., &amp;amp; Lembo L. (2009). Strategy instruction in writing for adult literacy learners. &lt;em&gt;Reading and Writing: An International Journal, 22(9)&lt;/em&gt;, 1021-1032. Access it online at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/sites/default/files/ALstrategy_sum_teachers.pdf" title="Strategy Instruction in Writing for Adult Literacy Learners: A Summary" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 1.231;"&gt;https://lincs.ed.gov/sites/default/files/ALstrategy_sum_teachers.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Math&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;The articles below provide guidance on how to help students develop number sense.  In addition to helping students approach problem solving in a systematic way, these materials will provide you with alternative approaches to presenting concepts to your students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="Using Part-Whole Thinking in Math" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Using%20Part-Whole%20Thinking%20in%20Math.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Using Part-Whole Thinking in Math &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="Two Ways of Thinking about Division" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Curry_Division_Thinking.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Two Ways of Thinking about Division&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="Revisiting Subtraction" href="https://www.terc.edu/download/attachments/13140423/Curry_RevisitingSubtraction.pdf?version=1&amp;amp;modificationDate=1456860707272&amp;amp;api=v2" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Revisiting Subtraction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
